data.text:
Finland. EnckellWithThant. Public domain image from Helsingin Sanomat.

The Finnish diplomat Ralph Enckell (1913–2001) hosting U Thant, the Secretary-General of the United Nations, in Tapiola, Espoo, Finland in 1962.

Finland. Pentti-Nikula-result-1962. Public domain image from Helsingin...

Photograph of the Finnish pole vaulter Pentti Nikula and his winning result, 494 cm, in Kauhava.

Finland. TawaststjernaNevanlinna. Public domain image from Helsingin S...

The Finnish musicologist Erik Tawaststjerna (1916–1996) with his friend, the mathematician Rolf Nevanlinna (1895–1980).

Olli-Puhakka-1962 - Helsinki, Finland

Photograph of the Finnish pilot Olli Puhakka at Helsinki Airport ("Seutula"), behind a desk.

Ahlberg-Linden-Wessman-1962, Finnish journalist

Photograph of three newscasters of Suomen Tietotoimisto news agency: Hugo Ahlberg (1930–1996), Kaj Lindén (1931–2013), and Kaj Wessman.

Ann-Christine-1962 - Helsinki, Finland

Photograph of the Finnish vocalist Ann-Christine Nyström-Silén (1944–) appearing in the television show Iskelmäkaruselli.

Icon Algot-Bostman-1962, public domain photograph

Photograph of the Finnish stage actor Algot Böstman (1935–2020) in his role as Daniel Hjort in the play by Josef Julius Wecksell.

Erik Bergman Von Schoultz Finnish writer, Finnish architect

Photograph of the Finnish composer Erik Bergman (1911–2006) and his wife, the author Solveig von Schoultz (1907–1996).

Four-Cats-1962 - Helsinki, Finland

Photograph of the Finnish vocal quartette Four Cats: Esa Laukka, Kai Ruohonen, Kai Lind, and Pentti Lasanen. They appeared in the TV show Iskelmäkaruselli.

Georg-Malmsten-1962, portrait, Finland

Photograph of the Finnish vocalist Georg Malmstén at Lennart Hyland’s show.

Vesa Jaarva perheineen, Finnish actors

Suomi: Näyttelijä Vesa Jaarva (toinen vasemmalta) perheineen 4.2.1964.Svenska: Skådespelaren Vesa Jaarva (tvåa från vänster) med sin familj 4.2.1964.

Jean Cocteau & Joel Rinne, Suomen Kuvalehti, Finland

Finnish actor Joel Rinne (right) in Paris in 1962, posing with Jean Cocteau (left).

Jorma-Reini-1962, military portrait, Finland

Photograph of the Finnish National Conciliator to be, Jorma Reini (1942–1998), during his military service.

Juhani-Harri-1962, portrait photograph, Finland

Photograph of the Finnish artist Juhani Harri (1939–2003). Public domain photograph, 20th-century male portrait, free to use, no copyright restrictions image - Picryl description

Jurkka-Ista-Palo-1962, Finnish actress portrait

Photograph of the Finnish actors Jussi Jurkka (1930–1982), Tea Ista (1932–2014) and Tauno Palo (1908–1982) when playing Period of Adjustment by Tennessee Williams at The National Theatre of Finland.

Kiila1962, Finnish writer - Helsinki, Finland

Photograph of the members of Kirjailijaryhmä Kiila (writers' group Kiila) board members at their meeting in Helsinki, Finland. From left to right: Sven Grönvall, Arvo Turtiainen, Tapio Tapiovaara, Jarno Pennanen.

Lilla-Teatern-1962 - Helsinki, Finland

Photograph of the Finnish actors Birgitta Ulfsson (1928–2017) and Lasse Pöysti (1927–2019) appearing together on stage at Lilla Teatern, Helsinki.

Maki-vs-Moore-1962 - Egypt - Helsinki, Finland

World Boxing Association World featherweight title match Olli Mäki (right) vs. Davey Moore in Helsinki Olympic Stadium, 17 August 1962.

Moore-Purhonen-Leskinen-Cotton-1962

Photograph of the boxers Davey Moore, Pertti Purhonen and Eddie Cotton with Miss Finland Kaarina Leskinen.

Paavolainen medal - Public domain photograph

Eino S. Repo, culture editor of Uusi Suomi and Apu, presented a medal to author Olavi Paavolainen (right) 10 February 1962. Suomi: Eino S. Repo, Uuden Suomen ja Avun kulttuuritoimittaja, ojensi mitalin kirjai ... More

Rannikko-Mayramaki, portrait, Finland

Photograph of the Finnish Jazz musicians Seppo Rannikko (1928–2000) and Pekka Mäyrämäki (1929–2015) at Old House Jazz Club.

Reino Helismaa ja Pentti Saarikoski 1962

Reino Helismaa and Pentti Saarikoski in 1962. (First published in Suosikki 5/1962.)

Sylvi-Kekkonen-with-writers-1962

Photograph of the Finnish writers Salme Setälä (left), Helvi Erjakka and Eeva Joenpelto with the First Lady of Finland Sylvi Kekkonen.

Tor Ragnar Nessling cropped to shoulder&head shot with hat

Tor Nessling, the General Manager of Oy Suomen Autoteollisuus Ab, in a presentation event of new Kontio-Sisu K-138SV model in Konala, Helsinki. Français : Tor Ragnar Nessling avec chapeau

Tor Ragnar Nessling - Helsinki, Finland

Tor Nessling, the General Manager of Oy Suomen Autoteollisuus Ab, in a presentation event of new Kontio-Sisu K-138SV model in Konala, Helsinki.

Triga-II-Otaniemi-1962, portrait, Finland

Photograph of the new Triga Mark II research reactor being presented to the press in Otaniemi, Espoo, Finland, before it was taken in use.

Hilkka-Kinnunen-1962

Photograph of the Finnish actress and vocalist Hilkka Kinnunen (1925–) in the role of Countess Mariza by Emmerich Kálmán in Helsinki, Rowing Stadium.

Alvar-Aalto-in-Uppsala-1962

Photograph of the Finnish architect Alvar Aalto and a model for his Västmanlands-Dala nation building in Uppsala, Sweden.
